      "title": "Composite Materials: Mechanical Behavior and Structural Analysis",
      "abstract": "Preface Trnslator's Preface Part I: Composite Materials 1. Basic Features of Composite Materials 2. The Constituents of a Composite Material 3. Moulding processes and Architecture of Composite Materials Part II: Basic Concepts of the Mechanical Behavior of Materials 4. Mathematical Basics 5. Stresses 6. Strains 7. The Elastic Behavior of Materials 8. The Mechanics of Deformable Solids Part III: Mechanical Behavior of Composite Materials 9. Elastic Behavior of Unidirectional Composite Materials 10. Elastic Behavior of an Orthotropic Composite 11. Off-Axis Behavior of Composite Materials 12. Fracture Mechanisms and Damage of Composite Materials Part IV: Modelling the Mechanical Behavior of Laminates and Sandwich Plates 13. Basics of Laminate Theory 14. Classical Laminate Theory 15. Effect of the Stacking Sequence. Mat and Cloth Reinforced Materials 16. Governing Equations and Energy Formulation of Classical Laminate Theory 17. Including Transverse Shear Deformation in Laminate Theory 18. Theory of Sandwich Plates Part V: Analysis of the Mechanical Behavior of Composite Material Structures 19. Cylindrical bending 20. Bending of Laminate and Sandwich Beams 21."
